        <headline>Heat Advisory issued August 17 at 1:19AM EDT until August 17 at 7:00PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Heat index values up to 95 to 98 degrees expected.

* WHERE...Eastern Ulster and Western Dutchess Counties.

* WHEN...From noon today to 7 PM EDT this evening.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat
illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
